Ukrainian boxing world champion
Vitali Klitschko, an opposition leader, is leading an opinion
poll for the countryâ€™s 2015 presidential election.  Klitschko was backed by 15.9 percent of Ukrainians in a May
21-30 survey of 2,030 eligible voters by the  International
Institute of Sociology , based in the capital, Kiev. His support
rose 7 percentage points from June 2012, the institute said in
an e-mailed statement today.  President  Viktor Yanukovych  had 14.3 percent backing, down
3 percentage points, according to the statement. The survey had
a margin of error of 2 percentage points.  About 18.1 percent of voters would vote against all
candidates, according to the poll.  To contact the reporter on this story:
